msgctxt "92_Ibuki"
msgid "Well, hello there, Kiryu-san. Glad to see you looking well."
msgstr "Buenas, Kiryu. Me alegra verte bien."

msgctxt "104_Kiryu"
msgid "Yeah, you too. It looks like the Honest Living Association is keeping you as busy as ever."
msgstr "Sí, igualmente. Parece que la Asociación por la Vida \\r Honesta te tiene igual de ocupado que siempre."

msgctxt "116_Ibuki"
msgid "It certainly is. It's no easy task for a former yakuza to start living on the straight and narrow."
msgstr "La verdad que sí. No es nada fácil para un ex-yakuza \\r empezar a vivir una vida recta."

msgctxt "128_Kiryu"
msgid "Yeah, tell me about it."
msgstr "Ya, dímelo a mi."

msgctxt "140_Ibuki"
msgid "Nevertheless, it's the HLA's job to support our members until they're capable of leading honest lives."
msgstr "De todas maneras, es el trabajo de la AVH ayudar a nuestros \\r miembros a llevar vidas honestas."

msgctxt "152_Kiryu"
msgid "Have you run into any more trouble with those hitmen who called themselves the Reapers?"
msgstr "¿Te has vuelto a meter en problemas con esos sicarios \\r que se hacen llamar los Reapers?"

msgctxt "164_Ibuki"
msgid "That's all cleared up now. A year ago their attacks were such a threat, we could hardly keep our operation running."
msgstr "Eso ya es agua pasada. Hace un año sus ataques eran de \\ tal magnitud que apenas podíamos seguir con nuestras operaciones."

msgctxt "176_Ibuki"
msgid "But thanks to you catching all the hitmen, things are going smoothly now."
msgstr "Pero gracias a que capturaste a todos los sicarios \\r la cosa por fin va viento en popa."

msgctxt "188_Kiryu"
msgid "Although one certain former Reaper does seem to still be hanging around and bugging you..."
msgstr "Aunque parece que cierto ex-Reaper sigue dando vueltas \\r y molestándote..."

msgctxt "212_Kotaro"
msgid "All right! Next time, I'm gonna work in an okonomiyaki restaurant! I mean, a guy's gotta eat, right?"
msgstr "¡Bien! ¡La próxima trabajaré en un restaurante de okonomiyaki! \\r A ver, uno tiene que alimentarse, ¿no?"

msgctxt "224_Ibuki"
msgid "You know, I still can't believe he used to be a hitman..."
msgstr "Sabes, todavía no me puedo creer que llegara a ser sicario..."

msgctxt "236_Kiryu"
msgid "Huh? I thought he just wanted to look tough but was too scared to actually ever kill anybody?"
msgstr "¿Eh? Pensaba que quería hacerse el duro pero \\r se arrugaba a la hora de matar a alguien."

msgctxt "248_Ibuki"
msgid "Oh, Kiryu-san. Don't let him hear you say that."
msgstr "Oh, Kiryu. No dejes que te oiga decir eso."

msgctxt "260_Ibuki"
msgid "When I asked him once how he could be considered a killer when he never killed anybody, he flew off the handle."
msgstr "Una vez que le pregunté cómo podia considerarse un asesino \\r si nunca mató a nadie, perdió los estribos."

msgctxt "272_Kiryu"
msgid "Hmm... Guess he's still got his pride then, huh?"
msgstr "Hmm... supongo que todavía conserva su orgullo, ¿eh?"

msgctxt "284_Ibuki"
msgid "I think you're right. Unfortunately, it seems his pride is causing him problems of a different kind now."
msgstr "Creo que sí. Por desgracia, parece que su orgullo \\r le está causando otro tipo de problemas ahora."

msgctxt "296_Kiryu"
msgid "With work, you mean? Yeah, from what I saw, it didn't seem to be going very well."
msgstr "En el trabajo, ¿no? Ya, por lo que vi no parece \\r que le vaya muy bien."

msgctxt "308_Ibuki"
msgid "It isn't. His jobs never last very long."
msgstr "No. No dura mucho en sus trabajos."

msgctxt "320_Ibuki"
msgid "He's always getting into arguments with the staff and customers, and sometimes even gets into fights."
msgstr "Siempre se mete en discusiones con el personal y los clientes, \\r y hay veces que hasta se mete en peleas."

msgctxt "332_Ibuki"
msgid "The problem isn't that he's lazy or anything. If anything, he's too serious."
msgstr "El problema no es que sea vago. \\r Es más, es demasiado aplicado."

msgctxt "344_Kiryu"
msgid "I get the picture. He thinks he's giving it one hundred percent, but that's not necessarily how everybody else sees it."
msgstr "Entiendo. Piensa que está dando el cien por cien, pero \\r no es así como lo ve el resto del mundo."

msgctxt "356_Ibuki"
msgid "Exactly. But, unfortunately, I can't follow him around his workplace and point out his faults."
msgstr "Exacto. Pero, por desgracia, no puedo perseguirle \\r en su trabajo y señalar sus errores."

msgctxt "368_Kiryu"
msgid "Well, he's not a kid anymore. He should be picking up this stuff on his own pretty soon."
msgstr "Bueno, ya no es un niño. Debería darse cuenta pronto."

msgctxt "380_Ibuki"
msgid "I hope so..."
msgstr "Eso espero..."

msgctxt "392_Kotaro"
msgid "I found a new part-time job! Yes! I rock!"
msgstr "¡Encontré un nuevo trabajo a tiempo parcial! \\r ¡Sí! ¡Soy lo mejor!"

msgctxt "404_Kiryu"
msgid "Don't you have to go for an interview or something like that?"
msgstr "¿No tienes que ir a una entrevista o algo?"

msgctxt "416_Kotaro"
msgid "Yeah, but I know they'll hire me! Who'd turn down somebody with this much energy!?"
msgstr "¡Sí, pero sé que me contratarán! ¿¡Quién le diría \\r que no a alguien con tanta energía!?"

msgctxt "428_Ibuki"
msgid "I admire your optimism..."
msgstr "Admiro tu optimismo..."

msgctxt "440_Kotaro"
msgid "I'm gonna go say hi and nail that interview!"
msgstr "¡Me voy a pasar por la entrevista y la voy a clavar!"

msgctxt "452_Kotaro"
msgid "Oh, almost forgot..."
msgstr "Ah, casi me olvido..."

msgctxt "464_Kotaro"
msgid "Thanks for the tea, Ibuki!"
msgstr "¡Gracias por el té, Ibuki!"

msgctxt "476_Ibuki"
msgid "Don't worry about it. Come by and see me any time."
msgstr "De nada. Pásate cuando quieras."

msgctxt "488_Kotaro"
msgid "I will!"
msgstr "¡Lo prometo!"

msgctxt "524_Ibuki"
msgid "You have to admit that he does seem to be making progress, even if it is only a little at a time."
msgstr "Hay que admitir que parece estar progresando, aunque sea poco a poco."

msgctxt "536_Kiryu"
msgid "Seems like it. I don't think you need to worry about him too much."
msgstr "Eso parece. No creo que tengas que preocuparte mucho por él."

msgctxt "548_Ibuki"
msgid "I know. I do worry too much. But I still feel like I'd like to check in on him and make sure he's taking to the new job alright..."
msgstr "Lo sé, me preocupo demasiado. De todos modos, todavía siento \\r que debo asegurarme de que se aclimata al nuevo trabajo..."

msgctxt "560_Kiryu"
msgid "I'm sure you've got a lot on your plate, though. Plenty of other people need your help, too."
msgstr "Me imagino que tienes mucho de lo que preocuparte. Hay \\r mucha otra gente que necesita tu ayuda."

msgctxt "572_Kiryu"
msgid "Tell you what. If I run into him around town, I'll see how he's doing."
msgstr "¿Sabes qué? Si me lo cruzo por la ciudad, \\r comprobaré cómo le va."

msgctxt "584_Kiryu"
msgid "You just take care of the rest of your Honest Living Association work."
msgstr "Tú simplemente ocúpate del resto de trabajo \\r de la Asociación por la Vida Honesta."

msgctxt "596_Ibuki"
msgid "Really? I'd appreciate that."
msgstr "¿De verdad? Te lo agradecería."

msgctxt "608_Ibuki"
msgid "If you do happen to see Kotaro in town, please check in on him for me."
msgstr "Si te cruzas con Kotaro por la ciudad, \\r comprueba por mi que esté bien."

msgctxt "620_Kiryu"
msgid "Will do."
msgstr "Lo haré."

